 JOHANNESBURG - Every once in a while a unique sport event, unlike any other event, showcases in South Africa. On Saturday the Down Syndrome Sports Club of Tshwane are hosting  their Athletics Day at Bestmed TuksAthletics stadium in Pretoria from 9am. More than 450 junior and senior athletes will be in action participating in a variety of track and field events.  For the past few months they have been training hard and undergoing specialised coaching in preparation for the big day.  The event is being live streamed as a sponsorship by 360Sport at www.streamit360.tv.